- Forget it. Let's go to the store.
- I'm staying.

258
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,820
Let's choose what you want together!

259
00:20:30,820 --> 00:20:32,850
- It'll be fun.
- Aren't you the loyal dog? Go by yourself.

260
00:20:32,850 --> 00:20:34,320
Come on already.

261
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:37,490
Why together?

262
00:20:38,330 --> 00:20:40,250
I'm home.

263
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:44,730
Ayaka, could we talk?

264
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:59,070
What is it?

265
00:21:00,580 --> 00:21:04,740
Isn't there something you're not telling us?

266
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:08,480
No.

267
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:17,080
You sent us 10 million yen after the wedding, isn't that right?

268
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,440
Yeah.

269
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:20,630
Where did that money come from?

270
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:25,360
It was money the Nitta family set aside for our ceremony.

271
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:30,280
Was that really all it was?

272
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:33,990
Did you think we wouldn't notice?

273
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:38,440
You married for the money, didn't you?

274
00:21:40,150 --> 00:21:42,910
Did you do that for us, for family?

275
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,800
Of course not.

276
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:50,240
I did it for my own sake.

277
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:55,210
I wanted money, so I entered a year-long contract marriage.

278
00:21:58,040 --> 00:22:02,840
You know, I've always admired luxury. Wearing fancy clothes,

279
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,130
living nicely, lavish lunches, and all that.

280
00:22:04,130 --> 00:22:06,130
living nicely, lavish lunches, and all that.

281
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:09,360
Basically, to be the envy of all.

282
00:22:10,230 --> 00:22:14,440
I wanted out of this lifestyle,

283
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:17,780
to experience what wealth was like, you know?

284
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,300
I'm sorry.

285
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:29,850
Why are you apologizing?

286
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:34,780
If anything, I'm sorry for lying.

287
00:22:36,420 --> 00:22:40,010
The contract only lasts a year.

288
00:22:40,010 --> 00:22:43,010
We'll make sure to act the part until it's over.

289
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:45,190
So don't worry about me, okay?

290
00:23:11,670 --> 00:23:13,380
Sis...

291
00:23:13,380 --> 00:23:18,620
[Kids' room]

292
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:20,680
They found out.

293
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:26,870
You should've told them the truth—that it was for us.

294
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:37,700
This might've been for the better, though.

295
00:23:45,890 --> 00:23:47,370
Here you are.

296
00:23:47,370 --> 00:23:49,980
Thank you.

297
00:23:49,980 --> 00:23:52,240
I'm sorry for visiting so early.

298
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,820
No worries.

299
00:23:57,530 --> 00:24:02,070
What did you need? Apologies for the rush. I have work soon.

300
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:09,250
I've heard everything from Ayaka.

301
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:16,130
As I understand, this was all a contractual marriage.

302
00:24:17,970 --> 00:24:20,010
What a disappointment.

303
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:24,850
Seeing you with Italian hot pot,

304
00:24:24,850 --> 00:24:30,220
I truly believed you loved Ayaka from the bottom of your heart.

305
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:43,470
I'm terribly sorry I've deceived you, Sir.

306
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:55,050
I want to believe it wasn't all a lie.

307
00:24:57,930 --> 00:25:03,260
Togo-san... don't you feel anything for my daughter?

308
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:09,150
This is our new seasonal dress.

309
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:11,990
The sparkling flowers along the chest-piece

310
00:25:11,990 --> 00:25:15,340
and glittery skirt is recommended for garden ceremonies.

311
00:25:15,340 --> 00:25:19,310
Togo-san, don't you feel anything for my daughter?

312
00:25:22,530 --> 00:25:27,070
[President's Office]

313
00:25:27,070 --> 00:25:31,130
- Please finish the documents I shared with you.
- Yes, Sir.

314
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:33,900
Nitta-san!

315
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:36,220
Is the project I left you with going well?

316
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:39,070
- Yes, thankfully.
- That's good to hear.

317
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:41,120
How has work been?

318
00:25:41,780 --> 00:25:45,170
Though the role of "President" still feels unfamiliar,

319
00:25:45,170 --> 00:25:48,730
Hachi-san and the wonderful staff have helped me along.

320
00:25:51,390 --> 00:25:55,550
Many reliable staff members have stayed. Please treat them well.

321
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:57,140
Of course.

322
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,990
Perhaps I also feel uneasy having my own room.

323
00:26:01,990 --> 00:26:03,200
How so?

324
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:06,460
I come from a large family; there was always a room shortage.

325
00:26:06,460 --> 00:26:09,490
A large family... sounds lively.

326
00:26:09,490 --> 00:26:11,810
What about your family, Nitta-san?

327
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:17,330
I'm acquainted with your father, but not so much with your mother.

328
00:26:20,950 --> 00:26:22,940
My apologies; that's prying.

329
00:26:22,940 --> 00:26:24,820
No, it's fine.

330
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:28,970
I'm sure to continue fumbling about, so I eagerly await your guidance.

331
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:31,840
Of course. Good luck.

332
00:26:33,590 --> 00:26:36,280
Hachi-san, when should we get drinks?

333
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:39,410
- I'll check your schedule.
- Thank you.

334
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:42,880
How about you join us, Nitta-san?

335
00:26:43,530 --> 00:26:45,610
I'd love to.

336
00:26:45,610 --> 00:26:47,240
Sounds great.

337
00:26:48,550 --> 00:26:53,930
You are "my" loyal dog; remember that.

338
00:26:55,310 --> 00:26:57,960
[Kamiyama Precisions]

339
00:27:09,460 --> 00:27:13,080
I've decided to close up shop.

340
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:18,930
Sorry, Son. I know you were trying.

341
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:22,530
But I'll be fine. Go back to America.

342
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:26,030
But I'll be fine. Go back to America.

343
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:28,010
I promise, I'll be fine.

344
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:47,230
Because... I trust you.

345
00:27:47,230 --> 00:27:52,270
I know for a fact that something is up.

346
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:15,010
Ayaka.

347
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:18,050
Come, sit.

348
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:32,910
Yes?

349
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:38,570
Your feelings have come across loud and clear.

350
00:28:39,940 --> 00:28:44,680
You're such a terrible liar. You always have been.

351
00:28:46,530 --> 00:28:50,880
Ayaka, leave the nest.

352
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:54,580
We've already returned the 10 million to you.

353
00:28:56,220 --> 00:29:02,320
Ayaka, your mother and I will manage.

354
00:29:03,220 --> 00:29:08,580
We want you to go build your own family.

355
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:14,450
Don't use your life for your parents, your siblings, or anyone.

356
00:29:14,450 --> 00:29:16,590
Live for yourself.

357
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:21,960
I expect you out of the house by tomorrow, okay?

358
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,690
Okay.

359
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:40,320
You should sit.

360
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:44,520
The doctor told me I need the exercise.

361
00:29:45,380 --> 00:29:49,020
You're a tough lady.

362
00:29:55,450 --> 00:29:57,420
Kin-chan...

363
00:29:58,540 --> 00:30:02,360
was I too harsh on her?

364
00:30:05,030 --> 00:30:11,030
I'm terribly sorry I've deceived you, Sir.

365
00:30:14,850 --> 00:30:19,590
I want to believe it wasn't all a lie.

366
00:30:20,690 --> 00:30:23,590
Don't you feel anything for my daughter?

367
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:26,970
Nothing at all?

368
00:30:27,730 --> 00:30:30,220
Not at first, no.

369
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:34,060
However...

370
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:39,080
my feelings now are true.

371
00:30:40,790 --> 00:30:42,700
Ayaka...

372
00:30:43,900 --> 00:30:46,280
is my one and only.

373
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:52,650
It'll work out.

374
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:55,570
Togo-san will make it work.

375
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:31,760
Togo, I brought us a drink to celebrate.

376
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:39,010
Where is Ayaka-san? Still at work?

377
00:31:39,010 --> 00:31:42,390
I bet you came because you knew she wasn't here.

378
00:31:42,390 --> 00:31:44,390
Goodness, what makes you say that?

379
00:31:44,390 --> 00:31:47,580
You are always good at telling lies.

380
00:31:47,580 --> 00:31:50,270
A terrible assumption, indeed.

381
00:31:51,290 --> 00:31:56,020
Nevertheless, I'm quite worried that she's out so late.

382
00:31:56,020 --> 00:32:00,220
There's no need. She's currently visiting family.

383
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:04,040
Then you must be hungry for dinner.

384
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,510
Shall I cook?

385
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:07,500
No, thank you.

386
00:32:14,950 --> 00:32:18,120
Did you and Ayaka-san have a little argument?

387
00:32:19,220 --> 00:32:22,840
You would know that better than anyone.

388
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:28,110
After all, you had Kamiyama-san approach Ayaka in the first place.

389
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:42,780
That sort of stunt won't break us apart.

390
00:32:43,410 --> 00:32:45,640
Whatever are you talking about?

391
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:48,990
Please end this farce.

392
00:32:48,990 --> 00:32:53,830
I've tried to live up to your expectations,

393
00:32:53,830 --> 00:32:55,320
always, without fail.

394
00:32:56,190 --> 00:33:00,270
Your cruelty had me in its clutches.

395
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:02,460
What are you saying?

396
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:06,360
I am your mother.

397
00:33:07,900 --> 00:33:12,070
You loved my rice omelets best of all.

398
00:33:18,220 --> 00:33:20,370
It's so good!

399
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:28,200
You are not my mother.

400
00:33:35,250 --> 00:33:40,590
♫ I was crying ♫

401
00:33:40,590 --> 00:33:46,170
♫ And recalled your face in order not to lose it ♫

402
00:33:46,170 --> 00:33:51,630
♫ Before it turns into a mental bruise ♫

403
00:33:51,630 --> 00:33:54,740
♫ I want to hug you tightly ♫

404
00:33:55,710 --> 00:33:59,520
[Prenuptual Agreement]

405
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:04,750
We want you to go build your own family.

406
00:34:07,460 --> 00:34:18,740
♫ Something like forgetting is also important ♫

407
00:34:18,740 --> 00:34:26,470
♫ Your spoken lines that don't suit you at all ♫

408
00:34:29,790 --> 00:34:33,110
♫ The colorful thoughts overflow ♫

409
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:35,820
♫ Nobody gets to see them ♫

410
00:34:35,820 --> 00:34:38,510
♫ I couldn't breathe ♫

411
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:41,320
♫ When the time stopped ♫

412
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:48,130
♫ I just kept looking into these eyes ♫

413
00:34:52,150 --> 00:34:57,160
♫ The reason for the falling tears ♫

414
00:34:57,160 --> 00:35:01,840
♫ You showed to no one ♫

415
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:04,560
♫ Pretending to be tough ♫

416
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:08,850
♫ I want to protect all of this ♫

417
00:35:08,850 --> 00:35:13,990
♫ The glittering bright heart tumbles through the air ♫

418
00:35:13,990 --> 00:35:19,730
♫ The flickering, floating heart becomes the wind ♫

419
00:35:30,140 --> 00:35:32,970
H-Hello?

420
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:38,100
Hey. It's been a while.

421
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:39,520
It has.

422
00:35:41,970 --> 00:35:44,970
Togo... we need to talk about Kamiyama-kun...

423
00:35:44,970 --> 00:35:46,890
There's no need.

424
00:35:47,620 --> 00:35:48,990
What?

425
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:51,570
It's over.

426
00:35:55,940 --> 00:35:59,920
Anyway, we have filming to do. Get here quickly.

427
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:03,210
- What?
- We'll start filming our morning routine at 7:00 a.m.

428
00:36:03,210 --> 00:36:04,740
At 7:00 a.m.?

429
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:06,460
Don't forget Negi.

430
00:36:06,460 --> 00:36:08,660
Give me prior notice!

431
00:36:09,530 --> 00:36:11,290
Riku, wake up.

432
00:36:11,290 --> 00:36:14,150
Get ready. We're filming today.

433
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:16,040
I see.

434
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:31,530
Stop, I'm bare-faced!

435
00:36:31,530 --> 00:36:33,700
- Stop!
- You look cute, though.

436
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:35,360
Hey.

437
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:40,620
- No running.
- You're too close!

438
00:36:40,620 --> 00:36:44,110
Terrible! This is seriously disgusting!

439
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:46,500
No problem! At least they're getting along.

440
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:48,250
Right...

441
00:36:48,250 --> 00:36:52,570
It's disgusting but... relieving, I guess.

442
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:58,170
- Hey.
- Yeah?

443
00:36:58,170 --> 00:37:00,200
I'm begging you to stop that.

444
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:01,470
It's eco-friendly.

445
00:37:01,470 --> 00:37:04,630
That watered-down liquid isn't tea. Go check your tongue.

446
00:37:04,630 --> 00:37:06,000
It's perfectly functional.

447
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,540
- Is not.
- Is too.

448
00:37:07,540 --> 00:37:10,850
Are you sure they won't get a divorce?

449
00:37:10,850 --> 00:37:13,500
Honestly? Not too sure.

450
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,380
Enough.

451
00:37:16,390 --> 00:37:17,940
I'll do it instead. Have a break.

452
00:37:17,940 --> 00:37:21,480
Thanks! I've been waiting for you to say so!

453
00:37:22,170 --> 00:37:24,210
- Hey.
- Yeah?

454
00:37:26,350 --> 00:37:28,170
Welcome home.

455
00:37:29,940 --> 00:37:31,880
Thanks.

456
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:38,740
- One bag per cup.
- What?

457
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:41,800
- That's such a waste!
- No, it's not.

458
00:37:51,730 --> 00:37:55,650
I apologize if I kept you waiting.

459
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,510
I'm honored.

460
00:38:09,740 --> 00:38:12,690
Part of me assumed you'd ignore my invitation.

461
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:16,680
I've wanted to meet you...

462
00:38:18,860 --> 00:38:20,530
Mother.

463
00:38:28,050 --> 00:38:30,640
Why won't you say a word?

464
00:38:34,030 --> 00:38:35,950
You...

465
00:38:37,790 --> 00:38:40,480
You are no son of mine.

466
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,960
Why...

467
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:47,270
won't you see me for who I am?

468
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:53,410
Togo is my only son.

469
00:38:53,980 --> 00:38:57,620
I don't know what you're conspiring,

470
00:38:57,620 --> 00:39:01,090
but please don't involve yourself with the Nittas any longer.

471
00:39:09,550 --> 00:39:11,440
The other day...

472
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:15,150
Father passed away.

473
00:39:24,290 --> 00:39:26,710
Before passing, he told me the truth.

474
00:39:28,730 --> 00:39:33,640
I always assumed you had abandoned me.

475
00:39:34,650 --> 00:39:36,580
But I had it all wrong, didn't I?

476
00:39:38,770 --> 00:39:41,630
You left my side...

477
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:46,000
to protect me.

478
00:39:50,150 --> 00:39:53,740
Please raise Arata for us.

479
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:59,040
I want this child to lead a life of freedom, of happiness.

480
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:08,360
I spent my days with Father and his relatives.

481
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,720
My life has indeed been happy.

482
00:40:13,260 --> 00:40:14,830
Still...

483
00:40:18,340 --> 00:40:21,300
I've always wanted to meet you, Mother.

484
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:29,520
Father loved you dearly.

485
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:34,210
He was constantly worried about your happiness.

486
00:40:34,210 --> 00:40:37,930
So he left his will with me.

487
00:40:39,250 --> 00:40:42,540
- Mother—
- Stop calling me "Mother," I beg you.

488
00:40:45,180 --> 00:40:50,070
I cannot become your mother, not anymore.

489
00:40:52,060 --> 00:40:54,920
Do not concern yourself with my affairs.

490
00:41:18,610 --> 00:41:21,630
Thanks for coming.

491
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:29,920
I'm sorry about how I acted the other day.

492
00:41:33,300 --> 00:41:36,470
I know an apology isn't enough.

493
00:41:37,570 --> 00:41:42,110
But those lies aren't easy to write off.

494
00:41:43,140 --> 00:41:45,330
I'm really, really sorry for tricking you.

495
00:41:46,220 --> 00:41:50,000
You had your reasons, though, didn't you?

496
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:58,570
The truth is, my father's factory has been on the verge of shutting down.

497
00:41:59,370 --> 00:42:01,840
With that blackmail against me,

498
00:42:02,950 --> 00:42:08,290
I was given money in exchange for breaking you two up.

499
00:42:10,550 --> 00:42:12,080
By whom?

500
00:42:12,970 --> 00:42:16,460
Nitta-san's mother.

501
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:21,000
Why would she do that?

502
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,920
I don't know.

503
00:42:23,680 --> 00:42:27,510
But I promise that's the whole truth.

504
00:42:32,250 --> 00:42:37,450
She'll most likely keep at it until you two are apart.

505
00:42:55,620 --> 00:42:56,720
Mother.

506
00:42:56,720 --> 00:42:59,640
♫ Although we are the worst couple ♫

507
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:04,290
Kamiyama-kun is a precious friend of mine.

508
00:43:04,290 --> 00:43:06,970
Why did you use him?

509
00:43:09,220 --> 00:43:14,580
I'm well aware I'm a disproportionate bride.

510
00:43:15,180 --> 00:43:21,400
But please spare the people around me.

511
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:24,810
- Even Togo-san—
- You know nothing at all.

512
00:43:26,830 --> 00:43:32,730
Take care to treasure your family and do them no harm.

513
00:43:36,260 --> 00:43:38,510
What do you mean by that?

514
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:42,560
♫ I rush to you as if by chance ♫

515
00:43:44,970 --> 00:43:47,110
Is everyone okay?

516
00:43:47,110 --> 00:43:49,370
What? Yeah?

517
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:51,740
Nothing's gone wrong?

518
00:43:51,740 --> 00:43:55,090
No. Why?

519
00:43:55,090 --> 00:43:58,730
Never mind, then it's fine.

520
00:43:58,730 --> 00:44:02,170
Sorry about that.
♫ Hey, together, one, two step ♫

521
00:44:02,170 --> 00:44:05,620
♫ I'm dedicated to you, dear my lover ♫

522
00:44:05,620 --> 00:44:10,670
In the moment, my sister remained blissfully ignorant.

523
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:18,990
[Haneda's Fishcakes]

524
00:44:18,990 --> 00:44:21,980
♫ Let's hope for the best  ♫

